table.name: COMMON_LOG_APPENDERS
table.Comment: Dictionary table for all appenders. Each appender defines the action of writing log information into particular Log Tables, with particular Priority

table.name: COMMON_LOG_DETAIL
table.Comment: Default table for "Detailed", or "Actual" Logging. All the log information from any pl/sql program must, by default, go in this table.

table.name: COMMON_LOG_DET_BKP_160105
table.Comment: Default table for "Detailed", or "Actual" Logging. All the log information from any pl/sql program must, by default, go in this table.

table.name: COMMON_LOG_EXEC
table.Comment: Default table for "Execution Logging". Data about all invocations of all public program units, must be stored in this table.

table.name: COMMON_LOG_EXEC_BKP_160105
table.Comment: Default table for "Execution Logging". Data about all invocations of all public program units, must be stored in this table.

table.name: COMMON_LOG_LEVELS
table.Comment: Dictionary table for all Log Levels (default: from DEBUG, to FATAL). Any custom Log Level can be added

table.name: COMMON_LOG_MOD_APP
table.Comment: Defines the Appenders used by each Module

table.name: COMMON_LOG_MOD_UNITS
table.Comment: Defines, from what PL/SQL Program Units, does each Module consist

table.name: COMMON_MODULES
table.Comment: Dictionary table for all system and custom modules
